    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix null pointer dereference in idft512 when called with NULL parameters\n\n### Summary\nThe `idft512` function in the NEON-optimized DFT implementation directly uses its input parameters `x` and `y` without checking if they are NULL. This causes a segmentation fault when the function is called with NULL pointers, which can happen during error conditions or improper API usage.\n\nThis issue also affects the related `dft512` function which had the same problem.\n\n### Reproduction\nCalling `idft512(NULL, NULL, 1)` or `idft512(NULL, valid_ptr, 1)` will cause an immediate segmentation fault due to direct dereference of the NULL pointers when initializing local SIMD pointers.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts_neon.c`: Added NULL parameter checks at the beginning of both `idft512` and `dft512` functions to prevent null pointer dereference\n- The functions now return early if either input parameter is NULL, preventing crashes and providing predictable behavior\n\n"
}